sourceResource.description: A few blocks from the state Capitol, shoppers at the Hmongtown Marketplace can buy just about anything. The bustling center of small businesses is a favorite of the city's Hmong community because if offers fresh groceries, medicinal herbs, and prepared food. But a June 2013 raid found that some vendors in the marketplace also had drugs for sale. Ramsey County Prosecutors charged 14 people with selling misbranded drugs, possessing and selling drugs that require a license, selling syringes, and unlawfully possessing poison.
